list_page_content.Completion Marks:
'''Completion marks''' are earned by completing specific objectives in ''The Binding of Isaac: Rebirth''. When completing these objectives, the post-it note on the character select screen fills up with Completion Marks. If objectives are completed in Normal mode, the completion marks are solid black. If objectives are completed in [[Hard mode]], the completion marks are outlined in red. Earning a completion mark in Hard mode will unlock marks for both Normal and Hard modes, even if the prior wasn't unlocked.

In ''Rebirth'', [[Mom's Heart]] / [[It Lives!]] is the only boss with a character-specific co-op baby unlock if you beat it in [[Hard mode]] instead of Normal mode, with one exception - {{i|Godhead}}, which is unlocked by obtaining every Hard mode completion mark with The Lost. as such, it is not necessary to earn every Hard mode completion mark to achieve Platinum God, only every Hard mode Heart mark, with The Lost as an exception. In ''Afterbirth'' and onward, every other regular character has a co-op baby that can be unlocked for earning all of their completion marks on Hard mode. There are a [[Mega Blast|few]] [[Mega Mush|additional]] [[Death Certificate|rewards]] for completing many or all completion marks.

In ''Rebirth'', there are 6 unique completion marks, and each one comes in two varieties, adding up to 12 marks in total. ''Afterbirth'' introduced 3 more, bringing the total to 17, as Greed mode only has one mark. ''Afterbirth+'' introduced 1 more, as well as an additional mark for Greedier mode, bringing the final total to 20. ''Repentance'' introduced 2 more, bringing the final total to 24. Each mark has a character-specific unlockable [[achievement|secret]] associated with it. There are 6 secrets per [[character]] in the base game, while there are 10 in Afterbirth, 12 in Afterbirth+ and 14 in Repentance.

{{dlc+|r}} [[Tainted character]]s have different requirements for unlocking secrets. One secret each is unlocked for beating timed challenges ([[Boss Rush]] and [[Hush]]) and main path bosses ([[Isaac]], [[??? (Boss)|???]], [[Satan]], and [[The Lamb]]). There are no secrets for beating normal [[Greed mode]], as well as no character-specific unlocks for earning all completion marks on Hard mode, bringing the secret total down to 7 per character. {{dlc-|r}}

