== Notes ==
* {{dlc|a}} As {{mode|Greed}} [[Greed mode]] is a unique mode separate from Normal or [[Hard mode]], it always appears on the completion note with the red outline otherwise found on Hard mode marks.
** {{dlc|a+}} This symbol is used to indicate completion of [[Greedier mode]], and the Greed mode symbol is changed to be one without a red outline.
* While it is possible to fight Mega Satan in the base game, Completion Marks for defeating him and their respective unlocks are only available in the subsequent DLC.
* In the base game, {{i|Godhead}} is unlocked by defeating {{e|Mom's Heart}}, {{e|Isaac}}, {{e|???}}, {{e|Satan}}, {{e|The Lamb}}, and {{r|Boss Rush}} on Hard mode as {{c|The Lost}}.
** {{dlc|a}} It is necessary to additionally defeat {{e|Hush}}, {{e|Mega Satan}}, and {{e|Ultra Greed}}.
** {{dlc|a+}} It is also necessary to additionally defeat {{e|Ultra Greedier}} and {{e|Delirium}}. This also applies to all other unlocks requiring beating all bosses on [[Hard mode]].
** {{dlc|r}} It is also necessary to additionally defeat {{e|Mother}} and {{e|The Beast}}. This also applies to all other unlocks requiring beating all bosses on [[Hard mode]].
* Some items and trinkets transform the current character into other [[character]]s. All Completion Marks earned in that run from the moment of death onwards will count towards the new character, not the old.
** {{i|Judas' Shadow}} transforms the current character into {{c|Black Judas}} upon death. Black Judas is considered the same character as {{c|Judas}} by the game and can earn all of Judas' Completion Marks.
** {{i|Ankh}} transforms the current character into {{c|???}} upon death, and {{t|Broken Ankh}} has a 22.22% chance to transform the current character into ??? upon death.
** {{i|Lazarus' Rags}} transforms the current character into {{c|Lazarus Risen}} upon death. Lazarus Risen is considered the same character as {{c|Lazarus}} by the game, and can earn all of Lazarus' Completion Marks. The only thing Lazarus Risen can't do is unlock {{c|Bethany}}.
** {{dlc|a}} {{t|Missing Poster}} transforms the current character into {{c|The Lost}} upon death if he's already unlocked.
** {{i|Clicker}} transforms the current character into a random character upon use.
*** {{dlc|r}} Only transforms into a character of the current side (i.e. Tainteds into other tainteds, non-tainteds into other non-tainteds)
* With {{i|Clicker}} and a reliable method of reaching the {{r|I AM ERROR}} room (such as {{i|Teleport 2.0}} or {{i|Undefined}}, held with a {{i|Schoolbag}}), {{s|The Void}} can be repeated endlessly and cleared with every playable character in one run.
** By using a {{i|Forget Me Now}} (and a method to duplicate it endlessly) this can be applied to any floor and boss in the game, allowing any Completion Mark to be obtained with every character in one run. A {{i|Crooked Penny}} combined with a {{i|Glowing Hourglass}} to rewind failures is a good approach. {{i|Moving Box}} will also be necessary to bring all of the required items on each reset.
*** {{r|Boss Rush}} requires the additional duplication of a {{i|Mama Mega!}} to repeat endlessly.
*** {{e|Mega Satan}} can only be repeated with the addition of other unlimited items that can unlock the door, such as a duplicated {{p|Get out of Jail Free Card}}, {{i|Dad's Key}}, {{dlc|a+|or {{i|Mr. ME!}},}} because the key disappears after a single-use. {{dlc+|nr+}} Mega Satan also has a 50% chance of automatically ending the run upon defeat, so it is only recommended to focus on that Completion Mark after finishing all other possible marks as the desired characters. {{dlc-}}
*** Completion marks for {{e|Satan}} and {{e|The Lamb}} are still mutually exclusive with Completion Marks for {{e|Isaac}} and {{e|???}}, as well as with {{e|The Beast}} and {{e|Mother}}. This means a minimum of four runs are required to obtain every character's Completion Marks using this strategy.
*** This strategy does not work for Greed mode Completion Marks, as Moving Box is not in any item pools (disregarding an {{c|Eden}} spawn and {{i|Spindown Dice}}).
**** Up to 3 Greed mode Completion Marks can be obtained in a single run using 2 or more items that revive Isaac as a different character – alongside 2 Forget Me Nows.
*** Getting all these items in a single run usually requires the use of a strategy to create infinite items and exhaust the item pool, like {{dlcalt|{{i|Blank Card}}|r={{i|Clear Rune|n}}}} combined with {{p|Jera}}. While this can be time-consuming to achieve in a single run, it can save the player a great deal of time and additional runs if they are are aiming for 100% completion.
** Substituting Clicker with items that revive Isaac as another character upon death will allow the player to get the extra Completion Marks for {{c|The Lost}}, {{c|???}}, {{c|Lazarus}}, and {{c|Judas}}, but will not allow for completion with every character as the Clicker does.
** Beating the game with multiple players will count towards each of the players' Completion Marks.
* {{dlc+|r}} [[Online (open beta)]] added a new {{e|Delirium}} icon and also blue and purple Completion Marks (only shown online). {{dlcalt|Blue is for Completion Marks that were completed in online mode only, and purple is for the Completion Marks completed in both Hard and online mode. (online is Hard mode only)|r+=Completing Normal/[[Greed]] mode runs online turns the Completion Marks blue, and completing Hard/Greedier runs turn the Completion Marks purple}}.{{dlc-}}

