There are 34 playable '''characters''' in ''[[The Binding of Isaac: Rebirth]]'', with 11 available in the base game and 23 available in the DLCs. Five of these characters ({{c|Isaac}}, {{c|Magdalene}}, {{c|Cain}}, {{c|Judas}}, and {{c|???}}) came with the original ''The Binding of Isaac'', while two additional characters ({{c|Eve}} and {{c|Samson}}) were added later. Eve was added in ''The Binding of Isaac''<nowiki/>'s Halloween Update, while Samson was added in the ''Wrath of the Lamb'' expansion. ''Rebirth'' contains four new characters ({{c|Azazel}}, {{c|Lazarus}}, {{c|Eden}}, and {{c|The Lost}}).

{{dlc|a}} ''[[The Binding of Isaac: Afterbirth]]'' adds one new character ({{c|Lilith}}), plus one more character via an update ({{c|Keeper}}).

{{dlc|a+}} ''[[The Binding of Isaac: Afterbirth †]]'' adds one character ({{c|Apollyon}}), plus one more secret character ({{c|The Forgotten}}) added via a [[Booster Pack]].

{{dlc+|r}} ''[[The Binding of Isaac: Repentance]]'' adds two characters: {{c|Bethany}} and {{c|Jacob and Esau}}.

''Repentance'' also adds alternate [[Tainted character|Tainted versions]] of all 17 characters. Tainted characters have their own set of completion marks and corresponding unlocks, however they only have a single unlock for completing both {{r|Boss Rush}} and {{e|Hush}}, and one altogether for beating {{e|Isaac}}, {{e|???}}, {{e|Satan}}, and {{e|The Lamb}}.{{dlc-}}

''Each character's progress can be gauged by checking their [[completion mark]]s.''

