== Trivia ==
* One common theory (which was [[edmundm:97038438355|confirmed]] by Edmund) is that all characters are different forms of Isaac himself. This theory suggests that every character is a creation of Isaac's imagination which he assumes the personality and appearance of when playing as them. Most characters represent different issues that Isaac believes he has, while ??? is Isaac after dying by suffocation inside [[The Chest]], Azazel is who Isaac sees himself as, and The Lost is Isaac's wandering soul (which can be seen upon dying).
** {{dlc|a}} Additionally, Keeper is Isaac's desiccated corpse, as evidenced by [[Ending 18]].
** {{dlc|a+}} The Forgotten could be Isaac's skeleton shown in [[Ending 17]] and [[Ending 20]].
** {{Dlc|r}} This theory is also confirmed by the cutscene before fighting [[The Beast]], in which Isaac briefly turns into The Lost, The Forgotten, and ??? as he grows angel wings.
* {{Dlc|r}} While on the character selection screen for the tainted characters, a male voice sings instead of the normal female voice, and the song is distorted. The same is true when loading into the game after selecting a tainted character.
** Also, when a tainted character is selected or being selected, the taskbar icon of the game changes to look like Tainted Isaac.

* In the ''Requiem'' expansion for the ''Four Souls'' card game, the tainted characters have their achievement names (e.g. "The Broken" instead of "Tainted Isaac") unlike in the video game. This was decided in a [https://twitter.com/edmundmcmillen/status/1393649169890385921 poll] made by Edmund via twitter.
** Before that, Edmund had posted an [https://twitter.com/edmundmcmillen/status/1393645830028992513 image] of Isaac's alternate version being referred to as "Tainted Isaac".
* When switching back and forth between the tainted and normal characters, you can see Isaac's face behind the Who Am I? note, which either appears as Normal or Tainted Isaac depending on which side you switch to.
* The closet you find any tainted character in is the same closet you see during [[Ending 21]]. This is reflected in how the characters you find inside the closet are usually hurt or damaged in some way, like how a child might look after being forced into a closet.
* Most of the tainted character's Delirium unlocks are their starting ability. Exceptions to this are Tainted Isaac, Tainted Lost, Tainted Keeper and Tainted Eden.
* Many, if not all, of the tainted characters have similar abilities to their non-tainted variants, with them having a "twist" on the original character that alters the playstyle in significant ways. An example of this is Isaac and Tainted Isaac, where the former uses D6 to reroll unfavorable items, and the latter automatically is presented with 2 options each pedestal, at the cost of an inventory allowing only 8 passive items at a time.

